		<div class="about about-transfers">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">What is the transfer fee?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p>All transfers, regardless of the bank to which the recipient belongs, are free.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">How much will I pay for a foreign transfer?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p>The price depends on the channel through which the transfer is carried out (online banking, branch, helpline),
							transfer mode (regular, urgent, express) and cost coverage options (OUR, BEN, SHA). To obtain the exact amount, please refer to the <a href="" class="no-redirect">Table of Fees and Commissions.</a></p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">When are funds credited to the account?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p>Both the bank from which the transfer is made and the bank that accepts the order have an impact on the deadline for carrying out the order. Posting incoming transfers to our bank takes place in three sessions (on business days): </br>
								<from class="bold">from 11 AM (1st session),</span></br>
								<span class="bold">from 3 PM (II session),</span></br>
								<span class="bold">from 5 PM (III session).</span></p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">Why was the transfer not completed?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p>The bank has the option to suspend any transfer in the event of reasonable suspicion. If this situation concerns you, please contact us.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">How do I cancel a transfer made to an incorrect account number?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p><span class="bold">Domestic transfer </span>- in the case of a properly approved domestic transfer, unfortunately it is not possible to withdraw such an order, we recommend contacting the recipient of the transfer. If this is not possible, make a complaint.</br>
								<span class="bold">Foreign transfer </span>- in the case of a foreign transfer, we have the option of accepting the order to cancel the transfer - as long as it appears in the block on the account. The bank does not guarantee that it will be possible to stop the transfer, a commission is charged in accordance with the TFC.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="about about-cards">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">What are the card fees?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p>The card fee depends on the type of personal account you have. Details of fees can be found in the <a href="" class="no-redirect2"> Table of Fees and Commissions</a>, in the card section. Calculation of the fee may depend on the number or value of non-cash transactions made - depending on the type of account you have, the conditions for exempting from the card fee may</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">What is the maximum amount I can deposit in the cash deposit machine?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p>The maximum amount of payments depends on the owner of the device. The cash deposit machine should display information on the maximum amount of one-time deposit or the maximum number of banknotes accepted at one time.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">When are funds credited to the account?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p>Both the bank from which the transfer is made and the bank that accepts the order have an impact on the deadline for carrying out the order. Posting incoming transfers to our bank takes place in three sessions (on business days): </br>
								from 11 AM (1st session),</br>
								from 3 PM (II session),</br>
								from 5 PM (III session).</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">How much does a credit card cost?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p>The amount of the monthly card fee depends on the type of credit card you choose.
								For Mastercard OK! The monthly fee for using the card is currently PLN 10. However, this fee can be easily avoided. It is enough that in the period from the last day of the previous billing cycle to the penultimate day of the current billing cycle, you make by credit card non-cash transactions for a total amount of at least PLN 600 (excluding transfers from the card's account).
								In the case of Mastercard TU and TAM credit cards, the commission for handling the card is PLN 19 and is charged once in each billing cycle. You can avoid it - it is enough that in the period from the last day of the previous billing cycle to the penultimate day of the current billing cycle you make a non-cash transaction with a credit card for a total amount of a minimum of PLN 1,500 (excluding transfers from the card's account).</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
