		<div class="about about-complaints">
			<div class="container">
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">What should a complaint contain?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p>The content of the complaint should include the following issues:
								Description of the event: it should be as accurate as possible. It is important to provide the amount and date of the event for financial complaints (e.g. transactions, fees, commissions). In the event of complaints about the quality of service, if possible, provide the name of the bank employee or the address of the bank's outlet. However, in the case of complaints about helpline employees, you need information about the phone number from which the call was made, date and time of the call and the consultant's name.
								Expectations towards the bank: - please provide your preferred method of resolving the complaint. The bank's goal is to meet customer expectations in this regard.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">How can I make a complaint?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p>You can submit a complaint or appeal against our bank's response to a previously submitted complaint in several ways:</br>
								At any Bank branch. It does not matter in which branch your account is kept. The complaint may be submitted to the banker either orally or in writing.</br>
								By phone via the hotline 24 hours a day, 7 days a week (*** *** ***; from abroad +48 ** ** ***)</br>
								Via online banking (after logging in, select the "Write message" option in the "Messages" panel)</br>
								By mail - by sending an application to the Bank's correspondence address (st. Something 34, 00-000 London)</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="question">
					<h3 class="faq-header">In what form will I get the answer?</h3>
					<div class="help">
						<div class="help-text">
							<p>Forms of response: writing, answer in online banking, SMS</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
